                    <span>At first, I wasn't sure I liked this book as much as Mr. Baer's first book "See No Evil." The early part of the book seems to rant quite a bit. But, the more I thought about it, if I were Bob Baer, I'd be mad too...and all Americans should be. The more books I read about 9/11 and al-Qaeda, the more I feel that it didn't have to happen. Obviously, it is easy to look at things in hindsight and say that. Mr. Baer does an excellent job of showing just how involved the Saudis are in terrorism (besides the obvious fact that 15 of the 9/11 hijackers were Saudi.) There are several scary aspects of al-Qaeda. What will happen when they attack again? What would happen if the House of Saud falls and radical Islam controls Saudi Arabia? What if the price of oil goes up to $145 a barrel? As usual, Mr. Baer writes in a very enjoyable style. The book makes for a fast read.</span>
                  
              
